In 1952, he moved to New York City.
He had been arranging for Stan Kenton since 1950 and continued to do so through the mid-1960s.
In addition, he wrote the music for the popular song "Young at Heart" (1953), made famous by Frank Sinatra and others.
Richards died October 7, 1968, in New York City, of a brain tumor.
